A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Chapter 1 of Title 31 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 general provisions regarding health, so as to provide for the right to contraception for
3 individuals; to provide for definitions; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting
4 laws; and for other purposes.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
6 SECTION 1.
7 Chapter 1 of Title 31 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to general
8 provisions regarding health, is amended by revising Code Section 31-1-20, which is reserved,
9 as follows:
10 "31-1-20.
11 (a) As used in this Code section, the term:
12 (1) 'Conception' means the process of combining the male sperm with the female ovum,
13 resulting in a fertilized ovum or zygote.
14 (2) 'Contraception' means a method of inhibiting the development of a human pregnancy
15 at any stage prior to conception.
16 (b) Females have the right to the use of any means of contraception. Reserved."
